(6, 36, 39, 'Ur very very welcome :-)\nHow''s the site goin?\nSo how did day 3 of toilet training go?\nHow u feeling????\nLooking forward to celebrating 2mrw nite?', 1),
(7, 1, 75, 'Hi Sharon,\nHow old is your boy? I''m still finding this site confusing! I know a beautiful family looking for a nanny share arrangement (me being the nanny) for their 2.2 yo boy. Let me know if you''re interested. My email is amelia.peacock@hotmail.com', 0),
(8, 1, 74, 'Hi Lara,\nMy name is Millie and I''m a professional nanny looking to fill up my days in 2015. Have you had much luck finding another family to share with? My email is amelia.peacock@hotmail.com if you would like to talk further. Thank you, Millie', 1),
(9, 1, 61, 'Hi Pip,\nI''m a professional nanny hoping to stay on with a lovely family in Bronte if we can find a new nanny share arrangement for 2015. They have a 20 month old boy and are looking for two days a week (flexible with days as mum works from home). If this is something you may be interested in my email is amelia.peacock@hotmail.com.\nThanks,\nMillie', 1),
(12, 74, 1, 'Hi Millie, thanks for the message.  We are looking for a family and nanny from late April/early May - we havent had any luck as yet', 0),
(13, 74, 21, 'Hi Amy,  We are a little family living in Chiswick near you and noticed that you are looking for a shared nanny this year - so are we :-)  We have a lovely little four month old boy Flynn and we really want someone lovely to look after him as I have to go back to work much earlier than planned in April or May at the latest.  My partner and I are from NZ, both have lived here for three years in Sydney.\n\nHave you had any luck finding a family and nanny? \n\nLara', 0),
(14, 74, 45, 'Hi Amy, \n\nWe are a little family living in Chiswick, looking to find a family and nanny to share the days with our groovy guy Flynn.  Flynn is currently four months old and I have to go back to work earlier than planned, late April at earliest or May/June if we can find the right family and nanny.\n\nWould you be interested in discussion our situations and seeing if perhaps we are a fit and secure a wonderful nanny for our little ones?\n\nI hope to hear from you.\n\nLara', 0),
(15, 80, 5, 'Hi Amanda,\nWelcome to Nanny Share Australia. This is Franciska, the founder of the site. It has come to my attention that there has been a technical glitch between Google maps and the layout of the ''create profile'' page. As a result, your profile may suggest that you have  ''0 family/nanny matches'' when in actual fact you may have many. The problem is linked to the address bar. If your suburb is not stated in the address bar, Google maps will find your street address which may well be in another country! To rectify this issue, we have reworded this page and ask for 2 minutes of your time to fix this problem. Please go to your profile, and select edit. In the address bar, ensure that you have entered your complete address as follows (street number, street name, suburb). Your postcode can be entered in the ''postcode'' bar and no suburb is required here. Apologies for this issue and I would greatly appreciate a reply message to confirm you have received this information and that it has resulted in matches in your profile. We are currently working on the backend to limit the search matches to a 40km radius. Thanks again for your patience and I hope the site takes of to help everyone find successful nanny-share or mummy-nanny arrangements!\nKind regards\nFranciska', 0),
