(138, 115, 57, 'Hi Simone,\n\nI''m looking for someone to share our nanny in Bronte. She works 5 days for us, looking after our 3 year and 18 month old boys. The 3 year old goes to preschool on Wednesday, Thursday and Friday, and we are looking for someone to share on some or all of those days.  We have a lovely Nanny called Kaitlin, who has been working for us since August 2014, and both boys adore her. She is friendly, polite, and wonderful with the boys, taking them out on regular excursions. She is great at following the routines I set for the younger one, let me know if things aren''t going to plan, and is always punctual. She left her job in a childcare centre to work for me, as she wanted a change from that environment, and her manager there was very unhappy to see her go. \n\nOur current hours are 8-6pm, and we would expect you to pay $15 per hour for the hours of care you needed, an even split of the $30 we currently pay her to look after two kids. Given the nature of the job, most parts are negotiable, ie days, start and finish times, and location. If this is along the lines of what you are looking for, I would love to hear from you!\n\nCheers,\n\nKim \n0411 444 442', 0),
(139, 123, 61, 'Hi Pip, \nMy name is Alida and I am very interested in the position you have advertised. \n\nI have recently finished working with twins and have just started a role on Tuesday and Thursday with a 2 month old baby. So I am available monday, wednesday and friday.\n\nI have 5 years experience as a nanny looking after children aged 6 weeks to 17 years old. I have had a previous nanny share position so understand the stress and craziness of dealing with 2 kids of the same age, I am also currently working with twins. I love engaging in craft activities to improve young ones motor skills and awareness of the world around them. I also love being outside and going on mini-adventures with the children I look after! I love to cook and take pride in creating fun meals which are both nutritious and delicious for kids.\n\nI have 9 years of experience working with children, my drivers license, first aid, working with childrens check, police check and I have a diploma in counselling and am currently studying for my diploma in chidcare online.\n\nI have worked with a range of kids through my time as a nanny including kids with ADHD, Autism and developmental delays. I am EpiPen trained and currently work for a family with a little girl who is severely allergic to a range of foods including nuts and wheat. \n\n\nPlease contact me on 0435544233 or email me at alidadreyer@hotmail.com. I can provide you with my resume and references. I look forward to hearing from you', 0),
