(200, 143, 156, 'Hello Emma, \n\nNo problem at all, i will tell you a bit more about myself!\nI am 19 years old and currently at university studying a bachelor of education (birth to twelve) which qualifies me to be a primary school teacher and a preschool teacher. I am currently in my second year of my degree. \nI have been working at Macquarie Ice Rink for 5 years, conducting children''s birthday parties, as a coach for children''s group lessons, as well as a coach of private lessons. \nI also work casually in two separate pre-schools (Only About Children and FitKidz). I also do some nannying and babysitting over the years. \n\nI am about to go on prac for university, and as a result i will be working at a school mon-fri 8-4. As a result of this, i would really only be looking at either evening or weekend work. I am also free most weekends, even if given short notice. So would be happy to help in any way that i can. \n\nI believe my profile mentions that i have my WWCC, first aid certificate, anaphylaxis training and am currently getting my police check (i did the online part of it today!)\n\nPlease let me know if there is anything more that i can do for you, \nIf you are interested in someone who would be available more often; i would be happy to recommend some people who are in my course and who are equally as qualified, and enthusiastic about children. \n\nFrom Harriet', 1),
