(287, 199, 120, 'Hi Meredith,\n\nI''m Erica Berkovich, I live in East Ryde and have come across your profile while checking out Nanny Share which I have only just discovered. I also checked if you happened to be on Ryde District Mums (which you are) because i recalled seeing your name before! I just wanted to get in touch to say hello. We aren''t needing anyone immediately for nanny service but it''s always good to know who is available and for how much. Feel free to correspond via FB if you like/prefer. All the best, Erica (and Alexander 7 & Bianca 3).', 1),
(288, 120, 199, 'Hi Erica\nThank you so much for contacting me and saying hi.\nYes, I am on Ryde District Mums. I love the page. Always great getting tips, best places to go with kiddies and recommendations  from the locals. \nWith all nanny share arrangements with a mummy nanny, it''s always negotiable.\nI''ve worked for many years as a nanny for families in the east and north shore. I have always been paid well based on my qualifications and experience. Mummy nannying is a lower rate due with the nannys child joining the arrangement.\nI have a delightful little boy (as they all are) who is now 19mths. \nAs much as it would be nice to have him make friends in a daycare environment, we all know those bugs lurk in childcare. Not an ideal situation if caring for children if I need to take time off to get him well! \nMummy nannying a better option. The family also gains for many reasons, but most importantly more one on one care in their own surroundings. \nI also do babysitting of a weekend should you be interested.\nMy number is 0402010274 should you wish to chat.\nThanks for contacting me\nMeredith', 0),
(289, 197, 51, 'Hello,\n\nMy name is Debora, I come from France and I am looking for a nanny job. I am not smoking at all. I have got a first safety degree, a childcare qualification specialized for children from 0 to 6 years, WWC and several experiences working with them. \nI am very patient, flexible, full of energy to spend but more than everything, I love children. I have taken care of kids from 3 months to 10 years. (nanny full time, nursery, leisure center) I have been lucky to have two little sisters that I have raised as often as possible.  I worked for three lovely families in London for a year and a half, and she gave me good references.\nAlso, I had a lot of pets when I were little so if you have one, not a problem for me, on the contrary. \nI will do my best to make your children happy.\n\n\nI will be very happy to meet you for an interview.\n\nPs : I have Working Holiday Visa for one year but it is with a pleasure that I can stay longer.\n\n\nkind regards,\n\nDebora', 1),
