(426, 340, 27, 'Hi Kelly, \nI am mummy-nanny to a 9 month old daughter and a fully qualified, experienced primary school teacher since 2009 with the Department of Education and Communities. I am just finishing my maternity leave and not ready to go back to teaching, so I am looking at working as a mummy-nanny. \n\nI am available as required. I live in Wolli Creek and have my own car (Mazda CX5 2013). \n\nI have my WWCC and I just refreshed my first aid certificate. I have also done extensive anaphylaxis and asthma training as part of being a DEC employee. \n\nAlthough I have not had any nannying experience, I taught at a daycare during my university degree (Bachelor of Education - Primary) in Wagga Wagga and feel extremely confident working with children of all ages and abilities. I also gained a lot of experience when working in London on Nursery classes (similar to pre-school here). \n\nI am organised, punctual and energetic and will happily explore the local community with your daughter by visiting parks, the library and any other age appropriate points of interest.\nI already take my daughter to RhymeTime at our local library, as well as playgroup and our home is filled with books, singing and craft. \n\nEnjoy your day!\nKind regards, \nErica Fletcher', 1),
