(127, 221, 115, 'Hi Kim, \nWould you be interested of nanny share on Thursday. \nI have a 2 years old boy\nMy nanny is great too\nDiana'),
(128, 221, 122, 'Hi Tessa, \nWould you be interested in nanny sharing on Thursday. \nI have a 2 years old boy, our nanny is great. \nWe live in Bondi beach \nDiana'),
(129, 167, 216, 'Hi Shaylee, so sorry for the very slow reply! I did respond but it may not have worked. Since then we have also bought a house so will be moving from the area - so no, no longer in a position to nanny share. Thanks anyway and all the best! Angela'),
(130, 167, 216, 'Hi Shaylee, hope my responses come through! No longer interested, thank you!'),
(131, 225, 217, 'Hi Sommer, \n\nMy name is Mel and I have a little girl named Halle who will be 11 months old next week. \n\nI saw your profile and thought your hours/rates were a good fit. Halle loves other children and is very social.\n\nOnly thing is we live in an apartment in Freshwater so not a lot of room for 3 kids at mine :)\n\nAnyway if you are still looking and are interested in meeting then that would be great. \n\nThanks, \nMel'),
(132, 226, 225, 'hello Melissa, are you still looking for a babysitter?'),
(133, 226, 221, 'Hi Diana, are you still looking for a babysitter?'),
(134, 226, 106, 'hello Orlagh how are you? are you still looking for a babysitter?'),
(135, 217, 225, 'Hi Mel, \nOur son, Angus is 13mo. He is a happy friendly boy who loves people and being outdoors. Our daughter Sophie is in Kindergaten this year so we primarily do not need care for her except for the possibility of after school. \nWe live in a house in cromer with a big back yard and are a short walk to the park. We would be happy to host but also to alternate. \nAt the moment we need Monday and Wednesdays for a nanny. Would this suit you? I would be happy to chat further if you would like. My mobile number is 0415811496. \nThanks\nSommer'),
(136, 229, 105, 'Hi yuliya,\n\nI am mummy/nanny with 2 kids. I am available tuesdays and wednesdays.  Let me know if you are interested. \n\nAlyssa'),
(137, 229, 223, 'Hi Virginie,\n\nI am a mumm/nanny with 2 children. I am available Wednesdays and charge $15 if I bring my kids to work.\n\nLet me know if you are interested. \n\nAlyssa'),
(138, 229, 224, 'Hi Andrea,\n\nI am a mummy / nanny with 2 kids and available Wednesday''s. I charge $15 an hour if I bring my kids. We are happy to come to you. \n\nAlyssa'),
(139, 230, 170, 'Hi\nMy name is Salam Kavvalos and I live in Belmore with my husband and son who is almost 5 months old. \nI am looking for a shared nanny 2 days a week (either Wednesday & Thursday or Thursday & Friday) to start in January 2016.\nI''m wondering if you''ve had any success locating a nanny and if you''d be willing to share.\nThanks, Salam'),
(140, 229, 219, 'Hi Natasha,\n\nI am a mummy / nanny with 2 kids and available Monday''s,  Tuesdays and Wednesdays.  I charge $15 an hour if I bring my kids.\n\nLet me know if you are interested. \n\nAlyssa'),
(141, 230, 89, 'Hi Lana,\nMy name is Salam and I have a 4.5 month old boy, Vasili. I am looking for a nanny to look after my son for 2 days a week starting in January 2016 (Wednesdays and Thursdays). I live in Belmore and work in Kingsgrove so am fairly close to you. \nPlease let me know if you are interested.\nSalam'),
(142, 230, 193, 'Hi Lauren,\nMy name is Salam and I have a 4.5 month old son Vasili. I am looking for a nanny for 2 days a week (Wednesdays and Thursdays) starting in January next year.\nI live in Belmore and work in Kingsgrove so am fairly close to you.\nPlease let me know if you are interested.\nSalam'),
(143, 224, 229, 'Thanks for your message Alyssa! We have been trying to work out what days the grandparents can do etc. it''s all so complicated ????\nYou aren''t available Monday''s by any chance? Our days keep changing? \nCheers, Andrea'),
(144, 123, 106, 'Hi Orlagh,\nMy name is Alida and I am very interested in the position you have advertised. \n\nI am available for an immediate start\n\nI have 5 years experience as a nanny looking after children aged 6 weeks to 17 years old. I have had a previous nanny share position so understand the stress and craziness of dealing with 2 kids of the same age, I am also currently working with twins. I love engaging in craft activities to improve young ones motor skills and awareness of the world around them. I also love being outside and going on mini-adventures with the children I look after! I love to cook and take pride in creating fun meals which are both nutritious and delicious for kids.\n\nI have 9 years of experience working with children, my drivers license, first aid, working with childrens check, police check and I have a diploma in counselling and am currently studying a triple diploma in chidcare, community services and counselling. All my studies are completed online and do not have any tests or assignments which would interfere with work in anyway.\nI also have a brand new car which I am happy to use.\n\nI have worked with a range of kids through my time as a nanny including kids with ADHD, Autism and developmental delays. I am EpiPen trained and currently work for a family with a little girl who is severely allergic to a range of foods including nuts and wheat. \n\n\nPlease contact me on 0435544233 or email me at alidadreyer@hotmail.com. I can provide you with my resume and references. I look forward to hearing from you'),
(145, 123, 205, 'Hi Daniela,\nMy name is Alida and I am very interested in the position you have advertised. \n\nI am available for an immediate start\n\nI have 5 years experience as a nanny looking after children aged 6 weeks to 17 years old. I have had a previous nanny share position so understand the stress and craziness of dealing with 2 kids of the same age, I am also currently working with twins. I love engaging in craft activities to improve young ones motor skills and awareness of the world around them. I also love being outside and going on mini-adventures with the children I look after! I love to cook and take pride in creating fun meals which are both nutritious and delicious for kids.\n\nI have 9 years of experience working with children, my drivers license, first aid, working with childrens check, police check and I have a diploma in counselling and am currently studying a triple diploma in chidcare, community services and counselling. All my studies are completed online and do not have any tests or assignments which would interfere with work in anyway.\nI also have a brand new car which I am happy to use.\n\nI have worked with a range of kids through my time as a nanny including kids with ADHD, Autism and developmental delays. I am EpiPen trained and currently work for a family with a little girl who is severely allergic to a range of foods including nuts and wheat. \n\n\nPlease contact me on 0435544233 or email me at alidadreyer@hotmail.com. I can provide you with my resume and references. I look forward to hearing from you'),
(146, 229, 224, 'Hi Andrea,\n\nI nanny on mondays.  Sorry about that.  \n\nAlyssa :-)'),
(147, 230, 226, 'Hi Ignacia,\nI live in the inner west of Sydney. Would you be willing to travel from Bondi?\nI''m looking for a carer starting mid January next year for my son who is currently 5 1/2 months.\nSalam'),
(148, 235, 135, 'Hi Angelica. I hope you are well. I''d like to apply for this position.\nMy name is Fabiana, I’m 25 years old.I’m mature, honest, reliable, cheerful person, calm, well prepared and I have driver’s license. I live in Maroubra as well. I work as a nanny because I love children and being with children is fun and challenging. I’m fascinated to help in it’s development, expanding my experience.\nIn the past, I had the opportunity to meet a lot of experience with children. \nCurrently studying Certificate IV of accounting at a school in the City.\nMy hobbies are traveling, meeting friends, cooking and more.\nI have police check, WWCC and more reference in Australia. I have drives license. \nDon’t hesitate to contact me if you need any additional information, it would be great to hear from you soon. If you want I can send my resume to you.\n\nWarm Regards,\nFabiana'),
