(25, 'CareerNanny', 'Susan', 'P', 'nannycare@adam.com.au', 'ea5cda3a1eebbb0ae0cbc175d8f1c846c132d6d5', 'ea5cda3a1eebbb0ae0cbc175d8f1c846c132d6d5', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, '0000-00-00', 'S.A Adelaide (Families around Adelaide)', 'fb3506f9475872e9d51d60e69f488924.jpg', '5000 Adelaide ', 2, '', NULL, 0, '', 0, '', '2', '1-2-3-4', '2015-02-04', '4-5-6', 0, NULL, '1 child $24+. 2 children share family $15+per family', '2', NULL, 0, NULL, '2', '1', NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, NULL, '20', '1', 'I''m a committed nanny who is focused on a loving and learning environment. I am dedicated to providing quality (long term) in home care.\n\nOpen to nannyshare AND/ OR  one family nannycare.', 1, 'Dear families,\n \nAfter obtaining a National Nannies certificate, I started my career in the childcare industry (2 years centre based) and then ventured to Sydney where I fell in love with nannying! I stayed 4 fantastic years with the same family, caring for 2 young children. (One from birth) On returning home I spent many years working for NannySA and privately, caring for lovely, professional families across Adelaide. (Including Doctors, a Surgeon and Psychologist) I was employed in long-term positions with children from ages 3 - 8 months onwards. Parents have described me as being, “caring, flexible, creative, intuitive, respectful, calm, extremely reliable, irreplaceable, and with an obvious genuine love for children”.\n\nI’ve only just finished working for a wonderful family with one gorgeous girl – and I was her sole charge nanny from 11 weeks to now almost 5 years old. As she will be starting school full time next year, the family will no longer need my care. \n\nI’m also thrilled to have had so much interest on Gumtree/other sites, and I’ve just secured a lovely family for 2015! This role will be a long term permanent nanny position (Monday and Tuesday) with a baby boy.\n\nI will therefore be seeking another very special family to continue my nanny career, to start around February / March + onwards in 2015 and ultimately long term. Ideally, a family with a baby, parents returning to work and hoping for a loving nurturing nanny, to become a part of their family and share in all the milestones. (On a 2 or 3 day a week - long term basis)\n\n I''m a committed nanny who is focused on a loving and learning environment. I am dedicated to providing quality in home care. Although exceptionally organised and tidy, I''m not a housekeeper / cleaner, I''m a professional nanny and seeking a family who appreciates and respects a loyal and devoted nanny / early childhood educator. \n\nAlong with my extensive experience in early childhood, I’ve studied and trained privately with National Nannies and completed a Childcare course. Training included lectures, tutorials and practical with exams.\n\nAs a qualified professional nanny, I have newly completed essential certificates and documentation:\n \n*St. Johns Ambulance first aid training (specifically customised for care of children & infants) \n*National criminal history check, enabling me to work with children\n*(On request only) GP’s letter stating I''m healthy; mentally and physically capable to work with young children. (Non smoker) \n\nMost importantly, I have glowing long-term references. \n\nUltimately I''m looking for the perfect fit and willing to wait for just the right family. I work best with organised, easy going families that have a good sense of humour and are highly communicative. (These attributes best describe my character) \n\nSeeking in 2015:\n\n•	2 full days a week position – open to 1-3 days for the right family / start date negotiable\n•	Wednesday, Thursday and / or Friday permanent part time nanny position\n•	Care of 1  / 2 children (3 months – 10 month old baby, highly preferable) \n•	Family wanting long term - permanent care \n•	Sole charge care (parents work outside the home) \n•	Family residing near CBD or surrounding suburbs of Adelaide\n•	Warm welcoming family, who just want the best care for their precious baby\n\nIf I sound like I might be the right match for your family’s needs in 2015, please email me. I''d love to hear from you. \n\nKindly, \nProfessional Career Nanny - ENQUIRIES: \nnannycare@adam.com.au\n \n \n \n\n\n\n'),
