(34, 'Mickii', 'Mickila', 'Jahnsen', 'kila_slash_15@hotmail.com', '1b1778a81a413f55704d0b1753cd26365376fe40', '1b1778a81a413f55704d0b1753cd26365376fe40', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, '1991-04-25', '43 Dudley st coogee,NSW,2034', 'c6fdae9569a9e240a2202d97f6db253c.jpg', '2034 coogee', 2, '', NULL, 0, '', 0, '', '3', '1-2-3-4-5-6-7', '2015-02-15', '1-2-3-4-5-6-7', 0, NULL, '$12.50-$15ph per family neg', '2', NULL, 0, NULL, '1', '1', NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, NULL, '6', '1', '', 1, 'Hi,\n\nMy name is mickii and I''m a 23 year old Australian nanny\n with over six years experience. I have my working with children''s check, first aid and glowing references! I have special needs, multiples, nanny share, crèche, daycare and baby experience. I have done other training in discipline  and development. \n\nI just finished up looking after a gorgeous 8 month old boy during the week! As he and his family are moving home to Ireland. I''m looking for a new role as of the end of feb beginning of march :) Please don''t hesitate to contact me :)\n\n\nThanks! \nMickii :)'),
(33, 'Gabriela', 'GABRIELA', 'DUMITRESCU', 'serenamilford@yahoo.com.au', '2b36b68d2d637d7283e66ead79b62e27be2c7d44', '2b36b68d2d637d7283e66ead79b62e27be2c7d44', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, '1965-10-31', '12/49 Bunnerong Rd Kingsford 2032', 'ee4645827af3fea8d907baeace398d36.jpg', '2032 kingsford ', 2, '', NULL, 0, '', 0, '', '4', '1-2-3-4-5-6-7', '2015-01-01', '1-2-3-4-5-6-7', 0, NULL, '$30', '2', NULL, 0, NULL, '2', '1', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, '18', '1', 'One of the most important skill is to observe the child, as every child develops different,and provide the right activities to match his level of development and contribute in achieving new skills. Learning should be fun, play is fun, then learn through play must be fun! Extra curriculum activities( dance classes, swimming, soccer...)could be part of a daily routine, trips to the Museums, City, Libraries, Aquarium . Working in childcare centres for so many years, I have gained the experience of setting up specific art and craft activities which help develop new skills through different concepts of that specific activity, like water play,coloring, mixing colors...and many, many more...\nFrench, Italian( worked for Franco/Aussie families since 2006 on daily basis to current day.', 1, 'Dear Family,\nThank you very much for taking the time in reading my profile, an opportunity to introduce myself. My background education is in Biochemistry and I''m very passionate about latest research regarding health so I am leading a very healthy life. After the birth of my daughter, I''ve discovered how much joy, love, affection a child can bring into this life and how little it takes to make a child happy so I decided to follow a career into the Childcare Industry. I consider working with children a privilege and wouldn''t change a thing! My first paid childcare role was in 1997 offered by Deli Community Service/Department of Community Service. Later on, was asked to join the Kooloora Department of Community Service/Playgroup coordinator role.While working for the Department, was asked to join the Out of School Hours team and Vacation Care run by the Randwick City Council. After 2 years the service ceased due to unforeseen circumstances so worked in a Long Day Childcare Centre for 5 years. Was so passionate about my work so I''ve decided to take further steps in completing a level of education and enrolled at TAFE and completed the Children''s Services Certificate III, while having 2 jobs, one at the childcare centre and a second one at OLSH Primary School, Out of School Hours and Vacantion Care.\nMy first role as a nanny was in 2006. Since then had various roles,the longest employment dated in 2008 til current day, for a family of 3, full time, sole charge, for many years, now just a day/week help with after school care. I have long experience working for Franco/Aussie families. \nDue to my extensive experience( 18 years)and working with families and children of different background, I have the ability to connect very quickly and settle very easily to new routines. I am very organised and the children in my care very tidy, well mannered, good eaters,happy, challenged, stimulated, active! Good with toilet training! You can see how we''ve spent the day,in pictures,short videos, photo albums and folders/walls full of masterpieces:) I am in touch with the family throughout the day, like, when leaving, where we are going, when we''ve back. Many times went to the doctors, Children''s Hospital, dropped temperature,administrate medications! My references are outstanding, showing the love,care,passion,dedication and hard work towards the children and parents in offering genuine help, so when they return home from a long day at work , they can interact with their little ones for a bit before bed time, dinner is ready and the place neat and tidy!Committed, trustworthy, flexible, reliable, punctual, responsible with a big love for children and first of all, understanding and complying to their needs, providing a safe environment with lots of age related stimulation. Current First Aid/CPR,Police check/working with children clearance. Multitasking with an eye for detail,show self initiative,running errands, prepare meals,(my meals are cooked from scratch, healthy, nutritious, continental), housekeeping, extra curriculum activities like, dance, gymnastic, swimming,trips to local Library,Museums, Sea Life,Wild Life, Water Play,Playgoup. My activities are planned after a close observation of the child as every child develops different so by providing the right one will help the child achieve new skills in a confident, fun way'),
