(42, 'Kyle', 'Kyle', 'Byrne', 'kylebyrne2035@gmail.com', 'ad48812e226372862ae80a294fff0eedb4fe7764', 'ad48812e226372862ae80a294fff0eedb4fe7764', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, '0000-00-00', 'Rainbow street,Coogee,NSW,2034', 'a2846ea7dba4934178af7e0b5d0a10dc.jpg', '2034 Coogee', 2, '', NULL, 0, '', 0, '', '5', '1-2-3-4-5-6-7', '2014-12-22', '2-3-4-5-6', 0, NULL, '28-40', '1', NULL, 0, NULL, '1', '1', NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, NULL, '9', '1', '', 1, 'Dear Families\n\nI''m a 27 year old Aussie male, looking for a family to work with long term or for at least the next year. \n\nI have 9 years experience with children from 6 weeks to 12 years old from many different cultural and social backgrounds as well as with children with differing mental and physical disability over the years.\n\nI completed my certificate III in 2012 and Diploma of Child Services in 2013 and have been working with children in a professional centre based environment since 2006, both here and abroad (UK). I am also a Austswim accredited swim instructor with a current First aid certificate, as well as currently studying Montessori based teachings to help in the implementation of lessons in practical life, sensorial development, literacy and numeracy activities.\n\nI am professional, caring, responsible, reliable, live an active lifestyle and more than capable of meeting all needs of the children.\n\nI believe children should have fun and learn through play based activities (direct and Indirect learning). That children should have choice and opportunities to succeed and fail. All children are individuals and will develop their own identities and skill sets in their own time and way.\n\nI have lived in the Eastern Suburbs my whole life except when traveling overseas, spending extended periods in the US, Canada and UK as well as short trips through Europe and Japan. I love to travel and will always have a desire to see the world, learn about other cultures and discover new adventures.\n\nI have all relevant documentation