(123, 'ALIDA.DREYER', 'Alida', 'Dreyer', 'alidadreyer@hotmail.com', '4adf2580cb56c2b05006625cc0070ff6beb65a14', '4adf2580cb56c2b05006625cc0070ff6beb65a14', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, '1990-08-11', '50 Cowles Road Mosman,NSW,2088', '8ed95937d0704d39085ac7ef8ce5b9f8.jpg', '2088 Mosman', 2, 'not a mummy nanny', NULL, 0, '', 0, '', '4', '1-2-3-4-5-6-7', '2015-08-17', '2-3-4-5-6', 0, NULL, 'dependent on share agreement', '1', NULL, 0, NULL, '1', '1', NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, NULL, '7', '1', 'Routine schedule planning for kids, Cooking, Music, arts and crafts, fun games, photography, Babies health, nutritional meal plans based on age and allergies, weaning onto solids, toilet training, setting discipline routines, weaning off bottles completely, weaning off dummies or attachment to toys/blankets', 1, 'I have been working as a nanny for the past 6 years. during my time as a nanny I have worked with a range of kids. Some of the kids I have worked with have had both psychically and mental developmental delays and severe allergies. I have had previous experience working with multiples and up to 6 kids so know how to juggle multiple tasks whilst ensuring your kids always come first\n\nI''m currently looking for fulltime work, I would prefer at least 40 hours in one position.\n\nI am a highly experienced nanny with a passion for caring, nurturing and assisting in the development of young children. I have been a nanny since I left high school in 2009,\nI have worked with a very diverse range of families on the North Shore, Northern Beaches and with in the Eastern Suburbs. Although I have extensive references from all parents that I have worked alongside, the proof is in the happy and healthy nature of the children who have been in my care! I am a family person who has been lucky enough to help care for my cousins, giving me very recent experience with newborns again yet also allowed me to shine as a nanny whilst helping my family with their growing families. Previous roles have included newborns to school age and also children with individual needs that must be met in accordance to doctors and specialists. I have had to cook and maintain meal plans for families and completely enjoy trying and challenging myself in the kitchen as well as having assistance from the children in my care, cooking is my passion and I placed first in the state for Food tech in the HSC \n\nI am comfortable with new borns as i have had experience with mother helping mums suffering post natal depression\n\nI have my first Aid certificate, am Epipen trained, and have attended work shops on nutrition for kids as well as workshops based on meal planning and awareness of kids and families with allergies. \nI am also currently studying a triple diploma online of Childcare, Counselling and community services\n\nI have my license and a brand new car which I am happy to use if one is not available.\nI have a full resume and up to date references available if you would like.'),
